					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The only time I saw unexpected sprite flicker in one of my projects was when I was turning off rendering early. Doing so at any time other than near the end of a visible scanline appears to interfere with refreshing the DRAM used for OAM, as sprites 0 and 1 get copied over some other even-odd pair of sprites.<br /><br />koitsu: The game is MineShaft, and it works fine on my PowerPak + NTSC NES, up to at least score 189.<br /><br />Download <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=104999#p104999" class="postlink">MineShaft alone</a> (reupload due to 403 error from fileden)<br />Download <a href="http://pics.pineight.com/nes/a53games.zip" class="postlink">MineShaft as part of Action 53</a> (#34, oversize BNROM)<br />Download <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=103762#p103762" class="postlink">Streemerz bundle beta 3</a> (requires <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?p=102718#p102718" class="postlink">mapper 28 plug-in</a>)</div>

